The Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, has de-registered over 70 political parties in the country. Prior to this exercise, there were 91 political parties in Nigeria. Prominent on the list of de-registered parties are National Conscience Party, NCP founded by the late legal luminary, Gani Fawehinmi; Peoples Coalition Party that came third during the 2019 presidential election; KOWA party and Fresh Democratic Party, which has presented Rev Chris Okotie as its presidential candidate since its formation in 2006.   Detail soon INEC receives average of 5 applications for party registration weekly – CPS Deregistration of 28 political parties Issues dog INEC’s moves to register more political parties